Author::::ID4027606
DateTime::::2016-03-08T14:23:50Z
Sometimes if it's a cold miserable day and I'm bored (I'm 74, so not often bored!) I have fun with cold callers. I'v got a selection of answers I use. The one about "our records show that you worked in a noisy environment" elicits the reply-"Yes, I ws an undertaker". Sometimes they ask to speak to me by name, but obviously haven't got a clue how to pronounce it, so I tell them "this is her secretry, can I take a message?". I got one poor little subcontinent guy going for ages--especially when he queried there being a secretary at a private address, to which I asked "doesn't your mothee have a secratary?" My best one is the dodgy computer fixer, I let him get as far as asking for my password, then tell him it's "B****r off!" Childish I now, but passes the time!



