Author::::DocDiv
DateTime::::2016-03-08T14:19:24Z
I once did cold calling for The Daily Express (or a subcontractor). We were trying to sell Express subscriptions to OAPs in Yorkshire (from a London office). One time I got a lady who had recently lost most of her sight, so informed me she was not really interested in a newspaper subscription. She was however hoping to catch a glimpse of a few blooms in her garden, as she was pretty sure that was going to be her last winter/spring. So I listened and cooed as she chatted about her garden for about 10 minutes. Catherine Shoard is right. Cold callers do have feelings! They let me go at the end of the week. As everyone who does the job is aware, your calls are monitored.



